be root
$ sudo -s

Update sources and packages
$ apt-get update
$ apt-get upgrade

Install needed packages
$ apt-get install sudo
$ apt-get install vim
$ apt-get install -y mailutils
$ apt-get install -y ssmtp
$ apt-get install ssh
$ apt-get install ufw

Add a non-root user
$ sudo adduser ehouzard

Add user to sudoers
$ sudo usermod -a -G sudo ehouzard

Switch to new user
$ su - ehouzard

Check
$ whoami

Edit sudoers file to avoid entering password each time sudo is used by adding following line
$ visudo
'
  ehouzard ALL=(ALL:ALL) NOPASSWD:ALL
'

// Memo
Check disk partitions
$  sudo fdisk -l

Check if up to date
$ apt list --upgradable
$ apt list --installed

Check running services
$ service --status-all

Lister open ports
$ sudo netstat -tlnpu

Check if a package is installed
$ dpkg -l {package_name}

// MEMO copy .ssh directory

$ sudo chown username file
$ sudo chgrp username file